Python scripts and report output screenshots

•	pip list - Data science libraries installed

•	hover_script.py and hover.png
      Source code:
      import seaborn as sns
      import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
      
      sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid", palette="muted")
      
      # Load the tips dataset
      df = sns.load_dataset("tips")
      
      sns.swarmplot(data=df, x="day", y="total_bill", hue="sex")
      plt.title("Total Bill by Day and Sex")
      plt.ylabel("Total Bill")
      plt.show()

•	mathplotlib_script.py and mathplotlib.png
      Source code:
      import pandas as pd
      import seaborn as sns
      import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
      
      # Load dataset (Power BI expects a 'dataset' DataFrame)
      # In Power BI, this line might be replaced by the data you feed to the visual
      # Example if your data is named 'dataset' in Power BI:
      # tips = dataset
      tips = sns.load_dataset('tips')
      
      # Create a Matplotlib scatter plot
      plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
      # Separate data by 'smoker' status for coloring, similar to your Plotly code
      for name, group in tips.groupby('smoker'):
          plt.plot(
              group['total_bill'],
              group['tip'],
              marker='o',
              linestyle='',
              label=name
          )
      
      plt.xlabel('total_bill')
      plt.ylabel('tip')
      plt.title('Total Bill vs Tip by Smoker Status')
      plt.legend(title='Smoker')
      plt.grid(True)
    
      # Display the plot
      plt.show()

•	numpy_script.py and numpy.png
      Source code:
      import seaborn as sns
      import pandas as pd
      import numpy as np
      import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
      
      # Load the tips dataset
      tips = sns.load_dataset('tips')
      
      # Example: Calculate mean total bill and tip grouped by smoker status
      grouped = tips.groupby('smoker').agg({
          'total_bill': 'mean',
          'tip': 'mean'
      }).reset_index()
      
      # Use NumPy to compute the difference between smoker and non-smoker groups
      difference_total_bill = np.abs(grouped.loc[grouped['smoker'] == 'Yes', 'total_bill'].values[0] - 
                                     grouped.loc[grouped['smoker'] == 'No', 'total_bill'].values[0])
      
      difference_tip = np.abs(grouped.loc[grouped['smoker'] == 'Yes', 'tip'].values[0] - 
                              grouped.loc[grouped['smoker'] == 'No', 'tip'].values[0])
      
      # Print the differences
      print(f"Difference in average total bill between smokers and non-smokers: {difference_total_bill:.2f}")
      print(f"Difference in average tip between smokers and non-smokers: {difference_tip:.2f}")
      
      # Plot total_bill vs tip, colored by smoker status
      plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
      sns.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', hue='smoker')
      plt.title('Total Bill vs Tip by Smoker Status')
      plt.xlabel('Total Bill')
      plt.ylabel('Tip')
      
      # Show plot (Power BI will capture this)
      plt.show()

•	plotly_script.py and plotly.png
      Source code:
      import plotly.express as px
      import seaborn as sns
      
      # Load dataset
      tips = sns.load_dataset('tips')
      
      # Create Plotly scatter plot with hover info
      fig = px.scatter(
          tips,
          x='total_bill',
          y='tip',
          color='smoker',
          hover_data=['total_bill', 'tip']
      )
      
      fig.update_layout(title='Total Bill vs Tip by Smoker Status')
      
      # Show the plot
      import plotly.io as pio
      pio.show(fig)

•	seaborn_swarmplot_script.py and seaborn_swarmplot.png
      Source code:
      import seaborn as sns
      import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
      
      sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid", palette="muted")
      
      # Load the penguins dataset
      df = sns.load_dataset("penguins")
      
      # Draw a categorical scatterplot to show each observation
      ax = sns.swarmplot(data=df, x="species", y="body_mass_g", hue="sex")
      ax.set(ylabel="Body Mass (g)")
      ax.set_title("Penguins Body Mass by Species and Sex")
      plt.show()

•	swarmplot_script.py and swarmplot.png
      Source code:
      import seaborn as sns
      import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
      
      sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid", palette="muted")
      
      # Load the tips dataset
      df = sns.load_dataset("tips")
      
      sns.swarmplot(data=df, x="day", y="total_bill", hue="sex")
      plt.title("Total Bill by Day and Sex")
      plt.ylabel("Total Bill")
